# PATCH: 005-disable-printing
# PURPOSE: Block all print paths — Ctrl+P, File > Print, window.print() JS API,
#          and print-to-PDF (which writes a file to disk).
#
# POLICY COVERAGE (policies.json "DisablePrinting": true):
#   - Removes the print menu item and toolbar button
#   - Blocks Ctrl+P / Cmd+P keyboard shortcut
#   DOES NOT block: window.print() called from JavaScript, or print-to-PDF
#   (a page can still trigger a print dialog and write a PDF to disk via JS)
#
# WHAT THIS PATCH MUST ADD (policy alone is insufficient):
#
# 1. JS window.print() API:
#    File: dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.cpp
#
#    Find: nsGlobalWindowOuter::Print (implements window.print())
#    Add at the top:
#      // ZeroFox: printing disabled
#      if (StaticPrefs::zerofox_printing_blocked()) {
#          // Silently ignore — same behavior as popups when blocked
#          return;
#      }
#
# 2. Print job initiation:
#    File: layout/printing/nsPrintJob.cpp
#
#    Find: nsPrintJob::Initialize or nsPrintJob::DoPrint
#    Add early return:
#      if (StaticPrefs::zerofox_printing_blocked()) {
#          return NS_ERROR_ABORT;
#      }
#
# 3. Print-to-PDF (saves a file to disk — must also be blocked):
#    File: layout/printing/nsPrintJob.cpp
#    The print-to-PDF path uses a PDF printer driver. It will be caught by the
#    nsPrintJob block above. However, also check:
#    File: toolkit/components/printing/nsPrintingProxy.cpp
#    Find: nsPrintingProxy::ShowPrintDialog and block there as well.
#
# 4. Remove the keyboard shortcut as a redundant block (UI layer):
#    File: browser/base/content/browser-sets.inc (or browser.xhtml)
#    Find the keyset entry for printKb (Ctrl+P / Cmd+P).
#    Wrap it in a #ifdef or remove it outright.
#    Note: DisablePrinting policy already handles this for enterprise builds.
#
# GENERATE THIS PATCH:
#   cd src/firefox-<version>
#   hg diff dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.cpp \
#           layout/printing/nsPrintJob.cpp \
